{"lemma":"سَمِيعٌ","slug":"سَمِيعٌ","root":"س.م.ع","root_slug":"س-م-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/س-م-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَمِيع","root":"سمع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":47},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20727"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"well-hearing","examples":[{"text":"مَثَلُ الْفَرِيقَيْنِ كَٱلْأَعْمَى وَٱلْأَصَمِّ وَٱلْبَصِيرِ وَٱلسَّمِيعِ ۚ هَلْ يَسْتَوِيَانِ مَثَلًا ۚ أَفَلَا تَذَكَّرُونَ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb سَمِعَ (samiʕa, “to hear”)."},"ipa":["/sa.miːʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20727","headword_ar":"سَمِيعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmiEN","text_ar":"سَامِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in six places. ―         -b2-  It is also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musomiEN","text_ar":"مُسْمِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Making to hear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (S, K.) Az remarks its being wonderful that persons should explain it as having this meaning in order to avoid the assigning to God the attribute of hearing, since that attribute is assigned to Him in more than one place in the Kur-án, though his hearing is not like the hearing of his creatures: he, however, adds, I do not deny that, in the language of the Arabs,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"smyE","text_ar":"سميع"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmiEN","text_ar":"سَامِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musomiEN","text_ar":"مُسْمِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but it is mostly syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAmiEN","text_ar":"سَامِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaliymN","text_ar":"عَلِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAlimN","text_ar":"عَالِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qadiyrN","text_ar":"قَدِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAdirN","text_ar":"قَادِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  Also ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Made to hear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"told;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man. (Msb.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u Als~amiyEi","text_ar":"اُمُّ السَّمِيعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amiyEaAni","text_ar":"السَّمِيعَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two long pieces of wood"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fixed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the yoke with which the bull is yoked for ploughing the land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}